EVT_8007315_DESC;Tensions between the military and communists increased in April 1965, when Sukarno endorsed the immediate implementation of the PKI’s proposal for a 'fifth armed force' consisting of armed peasants and workers. However, this idea was rejected by the army’s leadership as being tantamount to the PKI establishing its own armed forces. Sukarno started to fear of a military plot to overthrow him.

