EVT_8007609_DESC;When Israel gained its independence, Ben-Zvi was among the signers of its Declaration of Independence on 14 May 1948. He served in the First and Second Knesset for the Mapai party. He was elected President of Israel on 8 December 1952, assumed office on 16 December 1952, and continued to serve in such position until his death, being the person who held this post for the longest period of time.;;;;;;;;;;X;;;;;;;
