EVT_8007623_NAME;United Nations Partition Plan for Palestine;;;;;;;;;;X;;;;;;;
EVT_8007623_DESC;The UN created UNSCOP (the UN Special Committee on Palestine) on 15 May 1947, with representatives from 11 countries. UNSCOP conducted hearings and made a general survey of the situation in Palestine, and issued its report on 31 August. On 29 November, the UN General Assembly voted 33 to 13, with 10 abstentions, in favour of the Partition Plan, while making some adjustments to the boundaries between the two states proposed by it. The division was to take effect on the date of British withdrawal. Both the U.S. and the Soviet Union supported the resolution. The five members of the Arab League who were voting members at the time voted against the Plan.;;;;;;;;;;X;;;;;;;
