EVT_8007672_NAME;Pre-emptive attack of 1967;;;;;;;;;;X;;;;;;;
EVT_8007672_DESC;Straits of Tiran were regarded by the Western Powers and Israel as an international waterway but its legal status was the subject of international controversy. The Arabs believed that they had the right to regulate passage of ships while Israel, with the support of other major world powers, countered that the Arab claims were legally not supportable. In 1967 Israel reiterated declarations made in 1957 that any closure of the Straits would be considered an act of war, or a justification for war.;;;;;;;;;;X;;;;;;;
