EVT_8215004_NAME;Eastern Allies;;;;;;;;;;X;;;;;;;
EVT_8215004_DESC;During the early part of Second World War USSR continued its policy of non-intervention and even limited support of German actions in Europe as evidenced by infamous Ribbentrop-Molotov Pact. However, all the German-Soviet treaties were brought to an end by the German surprise attack on the USSR on 22 June 1941. The Soviet Union so entered in alliance with the United Kingdom. Following the USSR, a number of other communist, pro-Soviet or Soviet-controlled forces fought against the Axis powers during the Second World War. Soon, a situational alliance of ideological enemies bound close by struggle against Nazi Germany formed, and the great coalition of the Allies, Western and Eastern ones, fought hand-in-hand until the end of the war.

