EVT_8231014_NAME;Hans-Ulrich Rudel;;;;;;;;;;X;;;;;;;
EVT_8231014_DESC;Hans-Ulrich Rudel (2 July 1916  18 December 1982) was a Stuka dive-bomber pilot during World War II. The most highly decorated German serviceman of the war, Rudel was one of only 27 military men to be awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Oak Leaves, Swords and Diamonds, and the only person to be awarded the Knight's Cross of the Iron Cross with Golden Oak Leaves, Swords and Diamonds (Ritterkreuz des Eisernen Kreuzes mit goldenem Eichenlaub, Schwertern und Brillanten), Germany's highest military decoration. Rudel flew 2,530 combat missions claiming a total of 2,000 targets destroyed

